launch 3 instances with 3 different OS  (AWS , REDHAT, UBUNTU) , different region 1a 1b 1c, same security group , same key
edit inbound  rules NFS 
###################3
AWS Instance connect

rpmquery nfs-utils
systemctl start nfs-utils.service
systemctl status nfs-utils.service
mkdir /data

search efs
create file system
name and create click on file system id 
scroll and click network
go to manage change all the security groups as instances and remove extras and save and attach and then there is a second command
 sudo mount -t nfs4 -o nfsvers=4.1,rsize=1048576,wsize=1048576,hard,timeo=600,retrans=2,noresvport fs-039d798c91d1efe67.efs.us-east-1.amazonaws.com:/ /data
cd /data
cat > index.html
